&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent posts are available however some of these posts are being advertised to address a temporary need however the Trust has made the commitment to offer the successful applicant a permanent contract with the Trust. In the event that the need for this post ends, a suitable alternative post will be offered. Applicants should be aware that alternatives may require some flexibility on role and/or location.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking highly motivated, dedicated and enthusiastic registered nurses for an exciting opportunity to join the Northern Centre for Eating Disorder’s Unit (Birch Ward) based at West Park Hospital Darlington. We currently have vacancies for Band 5 Registered Mental Health Nurses to join the team. You will be joining an established, supportive multi-disciplinary team that is committed to delivering high quality, patient centred care. You will be working closely with a wide range of professionals’ in the team as well as external agencies who support the Eating Disorder service. We accept local and national referrals and liaise with services all over the country to support admissions and Community discharges. The successful candidate will provide a range of evidence based nursing interventions from initial assessment, nutrition, physical health monitoring as well as psychological focused interventions to support the patient’s journey whilst an inpatient. Working within the Eating Disorders service is an excellent opportunity to learn and develop a wide range of skills alongside the wider team. As an organization we are serious about supporting a diverse workforce that reflects our local community and are very much focused on being an inclusive and compassionate place to work. We are committed to the health and wellbeing of our staff and we have a number of initiatives and support for staff including access to psychology and counselling services. The Trust is committed to achieving high standards of health for its service users, staff and visitors providing a safe environment for staff, we operate a smoke free policy on all sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Northern Centre for Eating Disorders (NCED) offers both internal &amp; external training opportunities, which cover an array of topics from psychological based therapies to nutritional interventions and guidance. The NCED is accredited by the Quality Eating Disorders Network and the successful candidate will be an active participant in the accreditation process. . There will be opportunities to be trained in psychological interventions which are NICE approved such as MANTRA and SSCM as well as bespoke in house training covering a wide range of topics including the physical health needs of those individuals with an Eating Disorder. Being part of a Service Level Agreement with the University Hospital of North Tees presents opportunities for the successful candidate to learn and have a greater understanding of the MARSIPAN Guidelines and work alongside our colleagues from the Acute Trusts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NCED has a close working relationship with our colleagues in CNTW and work is progressing for the Trusts to become a Provider Collaborative. This will present opportunities to the successful candidate to develop the service even further. The service is already an active part of the Eating Disorders teaching and training forum and the successful candidate can access bi monthly training and teaching workshops. The NCED has a wide range of career progression and development opportunities. Having a Nurse Consultant in post supports the development of the nursing team and keeps the team updated on the latest research and development in eating disorders nationally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a service we work closely with the Community Team &amp; Day Service for Eating Disorders based at Imperial Avenue, Stockton-On-Tees. There are opportunities for the successful candidates to learn more about these services to support patient care but also to have a better understanding of the services available for the patients we care for on discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
